      "source": [
        "# KMeans From Scratch\n",
        "\n",
        "This Jupyter Notebook provides a detailed, step-by-step guide on implementing the KMeans clustering algorithm from scratch. It covers the following key areas:\n",
        "- Sample data points\n",
        "- Select initial cluster centers\n",
        "- Iteratively update cluster centers"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "![Reference_Ch3_part_1_kmeans_from_scratch.png](data:image/png;base64,)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8Pl09fXMWXYX"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 1,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CgieKwNyD15r"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import random\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "cmap = plt.get_cmap('tab10')\n",
        "colors = [cmap(i) for i in range(cmap.N)]\n",
        "\n",
        "mpl.rcParams[\"font.size\"] = 24\n",
        "mpl.rcParams[\"lines.linewidth\"] = 2\n",
        "\n",
        "seed = 0\n",
        "random.seed(seed)\n",
        "np.random.seed(seed)\n",
        "n_samples = 10\n",
        "markersize = 100"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tqvg6m47D15s"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Sample data points"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 2,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "8paiSH8UD15s"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Sample 10 points\n",
        "m1 = [1, 1]\n",
        "cov1 = [[1, 0], [0, 1]]\n",
        "s1 = np.random.multivariate_normal(m1, cov1, 5)\n",
        "\n",
        "m2 = [-1, -1]\n",
        "cov2 = [[1, -0.5], [-0.5, 1]]\n",
        "s2 = np.random.multivariate_normal(m2, cov2, 5)\n",
        "\n",
        "samples = np.concat([s1, s2])\n",
        "np.random.shuffle(samples)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 3,
      "metadata": {

        "plt.xlim([-2, 2])\n",
        "plt.ylim([-2, 2])\n",
        "plt.axis(\"equal\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",

      },
      "source": [
        "## Select initial cluster centers"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 4,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 538
        },
        "id": "o8DlBybdD15t",
        "outputId": "77fde63b-dbec-4626-e15f-465739bcc3f0"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "(np.float64(-2.659691942232599),\n",
              " np.float64(3.1307603678824707),\n",
              " np.float64(-1.3757641112226862),\n",
              " np.float64(3.4607340235073694))"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 4
        },
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 500x500 with 1 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "## any two clusters\n",
        "cluster_ids = [0, 2]\n",
        "centers = samples[cluster_ids]\n",
        "k = len(cluster_ids)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))\n",
        "plt.scatter(samples[:, 0], samples[:, 1], s=markersize, color=\"k\")\n",
        "plt.scatter(centers[:,0], centers[:, 1],\n",
        "            s=markersize*3, c=colors[:k], marker=(5, 1))\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.axis(\"equal\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "oS2i0IV4D15u"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Iteratively update cluster centers"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 5,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BDZbabbKD15u"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def kmeans(centers, data, steps):\n",
        "    k = len(centers)\n",
        "    losses = []\n",
        "    labels = []\n",
        "    for _ in range(steps):\n",
        "        distances = np.linalg.norm(data[:, np.newaxis] - centers, axis=2)\n",
        "        labels = np.argmin(distances, axis=1)\n",
        "        diff = data - centers[labels]\n",
        "        loss = np.sum(diff**2)\n",
        "        losses.append(loss)\n",
        "        new_centers = np.array([data[labels == i].mean(axis=0) for i in range(k)])\n",
        "        if np.all(centers == new_centers):\n",
        "            print(\"Converged\")\n",
        "            break\n",
        "        centers = new_centers\n",
        "    return centers, labels, losses"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qVSoRQ2wD15u"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Run one step iteration"
      ]
    },

      "execution_count": 6,
      "metadata": {

      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "new_centers, labels, losses = kmeans(centers, samples, 1)"
      ]
